<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900629-0041</DOCNO><DOCID>900629-0041.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Union Texas Petroleum Holdings:   Offshore Platform Planned   For Oil and Gas Production</HL><DATE>06/29/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A6G</SO><CO>   UTH I.AGI ALD</CO><IN>PETROLEUM (PET)OIL, SECONDARY (OIS)</IN><LP>   Union Texas Petroleum Holdings Inc. said it will constructa $74 million platform with processing facilities to produceoil and natural gas discovered on two properties it holds inthe Gulf of Mexico.   The Houston-based company said production from theplatform, to be located about 150 miles south of Lafayette,La., is scheduled to begin in 1992, at a rate of 60 millioncubic feet of gas and 3,000 barrels of oil a day.</LP><TEXT>   Union Texas is the operator of Vermilion blocks 412 and404, with a 50% interest in each. AGIP Petroleum Co., a unitof AGIP S.p.A. ENI Group, holds the remaining 50% interestsin both properties.   Union Texas, 40%-owned by Kohlberg Kravis Roberts andamp; Co.and 40%-owned by Allied-Signal Inc., recently said it wasputting itself up for sale and hired an investment banker toassist it in the potential sale.</TEXT></DOC>